OL,7,FKayleigh Chapman told the court: "My
OL,8,Fdad loved and appreciated life, he
OL,9,Ftook nothing for granted. He was
OL,10,Fvibrant and full of fun."
OL,12,FShe added: "My dad was a completely
OL,13,Finnocent bystander who didn't ask for
OL,14,Fthis to happen."
OL,16,FMs Jordan, a friend of Mr Darby, was
OL,17,Fthe most seriously injured of the
OL,18,Fsurvivors and nearly died. She said
OL,19,Fshe had suffered 20 fractures, was
OL,20,Fplaced in a coma, and stayed in
OL,21,Fhospital for six weeks.
